Instructions for updating SSL Certificate with Lets Encrypt:
1) Open the Virtual Box
2) In the terminal: cd letsencrypt
3) In the terminal: ./letsencrypt-auto -d <your-full-site-name> --server https://acme-v01.api.letsencrypt.org/directory -a manual auth -v --debug
--(Make sure to replace <your-full-site-name> with www.stlclassrooms.com as applicable)
4) Copy the filename into the routes.js section that directs to the SSL file
5) Copy the file data into the SSL file
6) Push the new data
7) Press enter on the virtual box
8) In the terminal: cd ../../../etc/letsencrypt/live/www.stlclassrooms.com/sam@sg-vh:/etc/letsencrypt/live/www.stlclassrooms.com
9) rhc alias update-cert node www.stlclassrooms.com --certificate ./fullchain.pem --private-key privkey.pem --passphrase ***********
--(Passphrase is standard)





///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
AUTOMATED VERSION:

0) Open the Virtual Box
1) In the terminal: cd ./letsencrypt
2) In the terminal: ./autoscript node www.stlclassrooms.com
3) Repeat #2 with any other subdomains desired
4) Suggested: restart server to clear challenges

NOTE: Make sure VM has internet